            "image": "shopify://shop_images/ENVE_SES_Pro_Tadej_Wheel-1043_bcfdbf11-a574-4025-b433-ac08b1730814.webp",
            "title": "PURPOSE-BUILT FOR THE HIGHEST LEVEL",
            "text": "<p>PRO in the name means it is a product developed in direct collaboration with the world’s top racers and represents the pinnacle of innovation—engineered and built for race-winning performance. The SES 4.5 PRO is the first product in our road line to receive the designation. </p><p>World Tour road racing requires an exceptional balance of aerodynamics, weight optimization, and compliance with governing bodies. The SES 4.5 PRO’s focus on the needs of professional racers requires compliance with the governing body’s equipment regulations. Depending on the course requirements, riders often choose 28 mm tires when road surface conditions are smooth and saving weight takes priority. With the 4.5 currently in the line where riders are most often pairing it with 30 mm tires, ENVE took advantage of the opportunity to create a purpose-built aero, climbing wheelset that isn’t intended to be the jack-of-all wheel, but rather a refined tool for climbing at World Tour speeds.</p>",
            "link_label": "",
            "link": ""
          }
        },
        "column_Na6DLn": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Hooked_Bead_Diagram_Comparison-3.webp",
            "title": "SES 4.5 PRO CONSTRUCTION",
            "text": "<p>New rim design saves 50 grams per rim over the SES 4.5. This is where the weight was saved. </p><ol><li>Reduced rim depth</li><li>Rim width is narrower</li><li>By removing material from under the Wide Hookless Bead ™ pinch-flat and impact function is preserved</li><li>A small hook is created as a result of eliminating material from Wide Hookless Bead ™ (critical tubeless dimensions preserved with new channel manufacturing technique)</li><li>Actual inner-rim width is maintained, preserving tire volume and rolling-resistance performance</li><li>New materials allow for thinner sidewalls and channel</li></ol>",
            "link_label": "",
            "link": ""
          }
        },
        "column_EWz7K8": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/enve_wind_tunnel_2025-0671.webp",
            "title": "AERODYNAMIC PERFORMANCE",
            "text": "<p>The foundation of the Smart ENVE System (SES) philosophy is the concept of Real-World Fast™ performance that goes back to 2009 when we partnered with leading aerodynamicist, Simon Smart. That means chasing maximum speed, but not at the cost of important performance attributes, such as weight, durability, and stability.</p><p>The SES 4.5 PRO meets these requirements by preserving the majority of the SES 4.5’s patented shape and therefore its best-in-class aerodynamics and ride characteristics. Simply put, after nearly 10 years, the SES 4.5 shape continues to punch above its depth. That’s how ENVE came to be the wheel partner of UAE Team Emirates. Unbeknownst to ENVE, UAE had purchased the leading wheels on the market and independently tested them in the wind tunnel and on the road. The rest is history.</p>",
            "link_label": "",
            "link": ""
          }
        }
